    <h3>When to Choose a Table-Top Wet Grinder Over a Tilting Wet Grinder</h3>
    <p>Choose a table-top model if: your daily batter requirement is under 15 kg, your kitchen space is limited, your budget is tight, or you need a secondary grinder for chutneys while the main grinder handles batter. Choose a tilting model if: you need more than 15–20 kg of batter per day, you want faster grinding with more powerful motors, or you're running a dedicated South Indian restaurant with high volumes.</p>

    <p>The key difference beyond size is the tilting mechanism — table-top grinders typically don't tilt, so you scoop batter out. For small batches (2–5 litres), this is manageable. For larger batches, it becomes tedious, which is why the tilting mechanism on larger grinders is worth the premium.</p>

